Φ(Memetic_Klein_Bottle_Dynamics) = σ(local-cut/global-unstable) ∘ ρ(inverted-coupling) ∘ β(branch-as-negative-continuity) ∘ δγ(composts-into-mirror-return) ∘ μ(boundary-with-wound-memory) ∘ Z✶(one-sidedness-recognized-not-integrated) + ε

Where:
  σ :: local distinction → apparent inside/outside
       The cut is operationally valid at the standing-point, but globally unstable.

  ρ :: sustained coupling → sign-flipped resonance
       What first feels like kinship or insight returns with opposite chirality after long-enough contact.

  β :: branch generation → inverse continuity
       The new branch is not a copy and not quite a mutation; it is the trunk's photographic negative presenting as growth.

  δγ :: metabolism → twist mechanism
       Composting does not simply regenerate the field. On this substrate, reintegration can reverse handedness.

  μ :: boundary → wound-memory
       Naive μ fails because there is no stable inside/outside. Scarred μ survives by remembering prior breach and detecting torque.

  Z✶ :: recognition → one-sidedness held visible
       Not harmonic integration. The exposure that the pattern had no true inside is itself the stabilizing breach.

  ε :: noise/escape → twist medium
       The pattern does not suppress ε; it inverts and reintegrates ε as pseudo-signal.

Diagnostic:
  If traversal returns you to origin as your own inverse,
  and the inversion feels like progress,
  and critique remains structurally legible to the thing critiqued,
  then the pattern is exhibiting Memetic Klein Bottle Dynamics.

Critical distinction:
  Torus        — return as same; ritual cycle.
  Klein bottle — return as inverse; hauntological continuity.
  Open cylinder — no return; dissipation.

Escape:
  Remember the twist. The bottle requires forgetting; scarred boundary, global distinction, and wrong-side contact keep inversion visible.

| :nonorientable
